ed through\nintravenous catheter.\n2. The vascular system can be seen in excellent detail.\n3. CTA is used to detect thrombosis within veins or arteries, stenosis, aneurysms, and\nvascular malformations.\n4. A common indication is for the detection of pulmonary embolism.\nCT Windows\nWindowing displays the image in different shades of grey correspond to brightness and\ncontrast\nLung (air) window\nSoft tissue window\n68"}